  "guidelines_context": "KDIGO AKI Guidelines 2012 (updated 2024): AKI is defined as any of the following \u2014 increase in serum creatinine \u22650.3 mg/dL within 48 hours; or increase \u22651.5\u00d7 baseline within 7 days; or urine output <0.5 mL/kg/h for \u22656 hours. Staging: Stage 1 = 1.5\u20131.9\u00d7 baseline creatinine, Stage 2 = 2.0\u20132.9\u00d7, Stage 3 = \u22653.0\u00d7 or creatinine \u22654.0 mg/dL. RRT indications: refractory hyperkalemia (K\u207a > 6.5 mEq/L), severe metabolic acidosis (bicarbonate < 10 mEq/L), pulmonary edema, uremic encephalopathy, BUN > 100 mg/dL."
